# dx_app — Cursor Rules

## Overview
dx_app provides 133 models across 15 AI tasks with Python (4 variants) and C++ examples.

## Context Routing
| Task | Read |
|---|---|
| Python app | `.deepx/skills/dx-build-python-app.md` |
| C++ app | `.deepx/skills/dx-build-cpp-app.md` |
| Async/performance | `.deepx/skills/dx-build-async-app.md` |
| Model management | `.deepx/skills/dx-model-management.md` |
| Validation | `.deepx/skills/dx-validate.md` |
| Always | `.deepx/memory/common_pitfalls.md` |

## Critical Conventions
1. IFactory pattern — 5 methods mandatory
2. `parse_common_args()` — no custom argparse
3. No hardcoded .dxnn paths — CLI args or registry
4. 4-variant naming convention
5. `logging.getLogger(__name__)` — no `print()`
6. C++14 only, RAII with std::unique_ptr
7. `dxrt-cli -s` before NPU operations
8. **Registry key ≠ Python class** — `yolov26` → `YOLOv8Postprocessor` (NOT Yolo26Postprocessor). See `.deepx/skills/dx-build-python-app.md` Step 5
9. **Search existing examples first** — before generating new code, check `src/python_example/<task>/<model>/`
10. **Output accuracy validation** — after smoke test, verify detection count > 0. See `.deepx/skills/dx-validate.md` Level 5

## Interactive Workflow (MUST FOLLOW)
- Ask 2-3 questions before building
- Present plan, get approval
- Validate after generation
- Output to `dx-agentic-dev/<session_id>/` by default

